-{"id":"frankenpandas-6xub","title":"[MEDIUM] fuzz: add fuzz_rolling_window_with_min_periods target (window/min_periods edge cases)","description":"Series::rolling and DataFrame::rolling expose (window, Option<min_periods>) but no fuzz target exercises the boundary conditions where window > len, min_periods=0, min_periods > window, all-NaN windows, or window=usize::MAX (panic-trigger candidate for arithmetic overflow).\n\nProposed target: fuzz_rolling_window.rs:\n1. Synth mode: 1 numeric Series, 4-32 rows, NaN injection rate from input bytes.\n2. window picked as min(N+1, raw_byte) so we exercise window > len; min_periods picked from a separate byte (None / 0 / 1 / window / window+1).\n3. Apply each rolling agg in {sum, mean, min, max, std, var, count, first, last, prod, median}.\n4. Asserts: output length == input length; all values prior to (window - 1) where min_periods is at default are NaN; never panics for any valid (window, min_periods) combination.\n\nNew fp-conformance pub fn fuzz_rolling_window_bytes(input: &[u8]). Stresses the partial-window handling that recent grouped-rolling work (br-x5oy/9uuq/4hkt) only tested at 2-3 fixed window sizes.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:24:04.003048692Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:24:04.003048692Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenpandas-6xub","title":"[MEDIUM] fuzz: add fuzz_rolling_window_with_min_periods target (window/min_periods edge cases)","description":"Series::rolling and DataFrame::rolling expose (window, Option<min_periods>) but no fuzz target exercises the boundary conditions where window > len, min_periods=0, min_periods > window, all-NaN windows, or window=usize::MAX (panic-trigger candidate for arithmetic overflow).\n\nProposed target: fuzz_rolling_window.rs:\n1. Synth mode: 1 numeric Series, 4-32 rows, NaN injection rate from input bytes.\n2. window picked as min(N+1, raw_byte) so we exercise window > len; min_periods picked from a separate byte (None / 0 / 1 / window / window+1).\n3. Apply each rolling agg in {sum, mean, min, max, std, var, count, first, last, prod, median}.\n4. Asserts: output length == input length; all values prior to (window - 1) where min_periods is at default are NaN; never panics for any valid (window, min_periods) combination.\n\nNew fp-conformance pub fn fuzz_rolling_window_bytes(input: &[u8]). Stresses the partial-window handling that recent grouped-rolling work (br-x5oy/9uuq/4hkt) only tested at 2-3 fixed window sizes.","notes":"cc-pandas triage 2026-04-22: triage note — DEFERRED (still open). Target exercises Series.rolling(window, min_periods) edge cases: window=0, min_periods > window, window > series_len, min_periods=0, window=series_len. Implementation shape: fuzz_rolling_window_with_min_periods_bytes reads window_tag (u8) + min_periods_tag (u8) + float_count (u8) + float_bytes (f64 LE), projects into a small Series, calls rolling(window, Some(min_periods)).mean()/sum()/std()/var()/min()/max(), asserts no panic + asserts output length == input length + asserts positions < window-1 are Null when min_periods <= 1 (pandas semantics). Template: fuzz_series_add_bytes. Medium effort. No blocker.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:24:04.003048692Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T10:45:23.975970885Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
