-{"id":"frankenpandas-aj8a","title":"[MEDIUM] fuzz: add fuzz_groupby_agg_dispatch target (HashMap+Vec aggfunc routing)","description":"fuzz/fuzz_targets/ has fuzz_groupby_sum but no coverage for the variadic agg dispatch surface that just landed multiple beads (br-715r dict-of-list, br-no1t transform_fn callable, etc.). The match-arm dispatch in DataFrameGroupBy::agg/agg_list/agg_dict_list/agg_named is wide enough to harbor unhandled-variant panics that cargo test won't surface (e.g. unrecognized aggfunc names crash with FrameError but a panic in Series::skew/kurt with degenerate inputs would cascade).\n\nProposed target: fuzz_groupby_agg.rs with:\n1. Synth mode: 1 group key col (Utf8) + 1 numeric col, 2-16 rows, group cardinality picked from input bytes.\n2. Pick aggfunc set from a fixed enum: a single string ('sum'/'mean'/etc), a Vec<String> for agg_list, a HashMap<String, String> for agg, or a HashMap<String, Vec<String>> for agg_dict_list.\n3. Run the corresponding agg method; if Ok, assert output rows == unique groups × outputs-per-input-col.\n4. If Err, assert it is FrameError::CompatibilityRejected (no panic).\n\nNew fp-conformance pub fn fuzz_groupby_agg_bytes(input: &[u8]). Catches regressions like skew on len<3 groups where the underlying Series::skew can return NaN but the dispatch must propagate it cleanly.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:23:52.080293314Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:23:52.080293314Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenpandas-aj8a","title":"[MEDIUM] fuzz: add fuzz_groupby_agg_dispatch target (HashMap+Vec aggfunc routing)","description":"fuzz/fuzz_targets/ has fuzz_groupby_sum but no coverage for the variadic agg dispatch surface that just landed multiple beads (br-715r dict-of-list, br-no1t transform_fn callable, etc.). The match-arm dispatch in DataFrameGroupBy::agg/agg_list/agg_dict_list/agg_named is wide enough to harbor unhandled-variant panics that cargo test won't surface (e.g. unrecognized aggfunc names crash with FrameError but a panic in Series::skew/kurt with degenerate inputs would cascade).\n\nProposed target: fuzz_groupby_agg.rs with:\n1. Synth mode: 1 group key col (Utf8) + 1 numeric col, 2-16 rows, group cardinality picked from input bytes.\n2. Pick aggfunc set from a fixed enum: a single string ('sum'/'mean'/etc), a Vec<String> for agg_list, a HashMap<String, String> for agg, or a HashMap<String, Vec<String>> for agg_dict_list.\n3. Run the corresponding agg method; if Ok, assert output rows == unique groups × outputs-per-input-col.\n4. If Err, assert it is FrameError::CompatibilityRejected (no panic).\n\nNew fp-conformance pub fn fuzz_groupby_agg_bytes(input: &[u8]). Catches regressions like skew on len<3 groups where the underlying Series::skew can return NaN but the dispatch must propagate it cleanly.","notes":"cc-pandas triage 2026-04-22: triage note — DEFERRED (still open). Distinct from fuzz_groupby_sum (which pins the sum path): this target should exercise the HashMap<&str, fn(...)> aggfunc dispatch in DataFrameGroupBy::agg_multi / agg_named. Implementation shape: fuzz_groupby_agg_dispatch_bytes picks an aggfunc name from a byte tag ('sum' | 'mean' | 'count' | 'min' | 'max' | 'std' | 'var' | 'first' | 'last' | 'nunique' | 'median') via modulo, then calls agg_multi(&[(col, aggfunc)]) on a projected frame; assert no panic + assert result has groupby-key column + aggregated value column. Shares the fuzz_groupby_frame_from_bytes template pattern. Medium effort. No blocker.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:23:52.080293314Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T10:45:12.842653920Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
