-{"id":"frankenpandas-arnn","title":"[LOW] fp-conformance assert_excel_roundtrip helper diverges from public default to satisfy reader; document as test-only gap","description":"Reviewing 989b/mxho fixes (cc): both excel round-trip helpers were patched to write with index=false because the default reader doesn't promote the leading index column back. Public write_excel_bytes default remains pandas-aligned (index=true). This is a test-only divergence — the harness now exercises a non-default code path.\n\nRisk: production users calling write_excel_bytes(default) and read_excel_bytes(default) will hit the same column-leak bug the harness sidesteps. The conformance suite no longer surfaces this regression because the harness avoids it.\n\nSuggested follow-up:\n1. Add a separate fixture (or augment FP-P2D-129/excel_round_trip_basic_strict) that writes with index=true and reads with the matching index_col so the default-pair round-trip is genuinely tested end-to-end.\n2. Or: ship a read_excel_bytes default that auto-detects the leading index column emitted by write_excel_bytes (via a sentinel header or 'inferred index_col' option) so the defaults round-trip cleanly.\n\nLow priority: doesn't block conformance-to-zero work, but the test harness is currently 'green for the wrong reason' on this surface.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:05:04.811757056Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:05:04.811757056Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
