-{"id":"frankenpandas-edjf","title":"[MEDIUM] fp-frame grouped-window code keeps unused agg_name parameter (r4au)","description":"Reviewing 2f80719 (br-frankenpandas-r4au, cod): The new as_index=true path through apply_grouped_rolling and apply_grouped_resample inserts 'let _ = agg_name;' (lines 28026 + 28075 of crates/fp-frame/src/lib.rs) to silence the unused-parameter lint after the refactor changed the closure signature. This is a code smell:\n\n- Marking a parameter as 'let _ =' instead of removing it from the function signature signals incomplete refactor and forces every caller to pass a value the body never reads.\n- Removes the documentation contract that 'agg_name' was used to identify the aggregation in error messages or evidence ledgers — future maintainers won't know whether to plumb it through or drop it entirely.\n\nSuggested fix: either thread agg_name into the new path (e.g. wrap errors with op_name, or stamp it into the per-group evidence record) or remove it from the apply_grouped_rolling/apply_grouped_resample helpers entirely and update both call sites. Pick one — don't leave _ markers.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:04:04.849224677Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:04:04.849224677Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
