-{"id":"frankenpandas-myra","title":"[MEDIUM] fuzz: add fuzz_semantic_eq_invariants target (lock pxv5 Null-bridging invariants)","description":"br-frankenpandas-pxv5 just added a Null(_)/Null(_) bridge to Scalar::semantic_eq. The existing fuzz corpus has no target that exercises the semantic_eq lattice, which means future regressions to that bridge (or to the Float64<->Null(NaN) bridge) won't be caught by fuzz.\n\nProposed target: fuzz_semantic_eq.rs:\n1. Read 4 byte tags: dtype_a, dtype_b, value_a, value_b. Build Scalar a and b from each (using fuzz_feather_scalar_for_dtype-style projection).\n2. Call a.semantic_eq(&b) and b.semantic_eq(&a) and assert symmetric.\n3. Assert reflexive: x.semantic_eq(&x) is always true (including x = Null(NaN), Null(Null), Null(NaT), NaN-Float64).\n4. Assert that any pair of Null(_) variants returns true (locks the pxv5 contract).\n5. Assert that Float64(NaN).semantic_eq(Null(NaN)) is true and that Float64(NaN).semantic_eq(Null(Null)) is also true (both are missing).\n6. Never panics on any byte input.\n\nNew fp-conformance pub fn fuzz_semantic_eq_bytes(input: &[u8]). Locks the equivalence-relation invariants (reflexive/symmetric/null-bridge) so the next refactor of semantic_eq can't silently break oracle parity downstream.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:24:20.601487209Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:24:20.601487209Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
