-{"id":"frankenpandas-s5cj","title":"[MEDIUM] fuzz: add fuzz_dataframe_eval_expression target (string expr -> eval injection surface)","description":"fp-conformance dispatches DataFrameEval/Query operations through eval_str_with_locals/query_str_with_locals — string expression parsing surface that has no fuzz target. This is a high-risk parser surface (similar to CSV/JSON in attack surface) with no adversarial coverage.\n\nProposed target: fuzz_dataframe_eval.rs:\n1. Synth mode: split bytes into (dtype_byte, expr_bytes). Build a small DataFrame with 2-4 numeric columns named a/b/c/d. Treat expr_bytes as a UTF-8 string (using lossy decode so all bytes are valid input).\n2. Call eval_str_with_locals(&expr_str, &frame, &locals, &policy, &mut ledger).\n3. Assert: never panics for any input. Errors are FrameError::CompatibilityRejected or ExprError variants — not unwraps or arithmetic overflow panics.\n4. For successful evals, assert output Series length == frame index length.\n\nNew fp-conformance pub fn fuzz_dataframe_eval_bytes(input: &[u8]). Catches parser regressions, expression-injection vectors, and arithmetic-overflow panics in the eval path — none of which are currently covered.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:24:32.787902592Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:24:32.787902592Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
