-{"id":"frankenpandas-x4ud","title":"[MEDIUM] fp-conformance bootstrap_cases needs differential evidence ledger emission for the 37 remaining fixture failures","description":"Reviewing packet_suite_is_green_for_bootstrap_cases: with cc's pxv5 semantic_eq fix landed, fixture-level results moved from 1141/108 → 1212/37. The 37 remaining failures span at least 18 distinct case_ids (dataframe_resample_*, series_dt_ceil/date_*, dataframe_pct_change/skew/round/value_counts/diff/abs/astype/memory_usage with_nulls variants, str_repeat_n / str_sub gaps).\n\nCurrently the harness logs only 'evidence_records: 0' for each Pass case and {report:?} as a single Debug dump on failure. There is no on-disk evidence ledger that captures per-fixture diffs in a machine-readable form — so each agent picking up a fixture fix has to re-run the harness, parse the {report:?} blob, and rediscover which case to fix.\n\nSuggested follow-up:\n1. In every Fail CaseResult, emit an evidence record (already counted as 'evidence_records' field) containing {expected_dtype, actual_dtype, first_mismatch_idx, first_mismatch_actual, first_mismatch_expected, ledger_id} via fp_runtime::EvidenceLedger.\n2. Persist the ledger as JSONL artifacts under artifacts/conformance/<packet_id>/<case_id>.jsonl so subsequent reviewers can  for known-failing-pattern signatures (e.g. 'all dataframe_resample_*_with_nulls share the same root cause').\n3. Add an --emit-evidence flag to fp-conformance-cli so CI can produce evidence in a single pass without rerunning per-test.\n\nThis is testing-harness hardening, not parity work; pairs naturally with 44vd (cascade-surface).","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:04:52.930570752Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:04:52.930570752Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
